  <sect2 role="installation">
    <title>Installation de Thunar</title>

    <para revision="sysv">
      Tout d'abord, évitez d'installer un fichier systemd non utilisé&nbsp;:
    </para>

<screen revision="sysv"><userinput>sed -i 's/\tinstall-systemd_userDATA/\t/' Makefile.in
</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Installez <application>Thunar</application> en exécutant les commandes
suivantes&nbsp;:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>./configure --prefix=/usr \
            --sysconfdir=/etc \
            --docdir=/usr/share/doc/thunar-&thunar-version; &amp;&amp;
make</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Ce paquet n'a pas de suite de tests.
    </para>

    <para>
      Maintenant, en tant qu'utilisateur <systemitem
class="username">root</systemitem>&nbsp;:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>make install</userinput></screen>

  </sect2>

  <sect2 role="content">
    <title>Contenu</title>

    <segmentedlist>
      <segtitle>Programmes installés</segtitle>
      <segtitle>Bibliothèque installée</segtitle>
      <segtitle>Répertoires installés</segtitle>

      <seglistitem>
        <seg>
          Thunar (lien symbolique vers thunar), thunar et thunar-settings
        </seg>
        <seg>
          <!--,
Those shouldn't be listed as libraries, since they are not accessible
by "-l something"
          thunar-apr.so,
          thunar-sbr.so,
          thunar-uca.so,
          thunar-wallpaper-plugin.so, and
          libthunar-tpa.so-->
libthunarx-3.so
        </seg>
        <seg>
          <!-- installed earlier (by xfconf presumably) /usr/lib/xfce4, -->
<!--,
installed by libxfce4util          /usr/share/xfce4-->
/etc/xdg/Thunar, /usr/include/thunarx-3, /usr/lib/Thunar,
/usr/lib/thunarx-3, /usr/share/Thunar,
/usr/share/doc/thunar-&thunar-version;, et /usr/share/gtk-doc/html/thunarx
        </seg>
      </seglistitem>
    </segmentedlist>

